  "dct_description_sm": [
    "Hong Kong Orthoimagery is a set of digital orthophotos representing Hong Kong. The dataset is comprised of nine tiles; the photos were taken in 2002 and 2004 and have a .6 meter resolution. The tiles may be downloaded through the Hong Kong Orthoimagery Index, a polygon layer that serves as an index for the orthroimagery tiles. The index can be downloaded through the link below, the URLs needed to download the tiles is embedded in the attribute information the index."
